.error
  %h1
    Ehm, you seem a bit lost, sir. Maybe going to the
    %a{ :href => root_path, :rel => "home" } list of projects
    will help?
  %dl
    %dt Ouch. This is a 404 error-thingie, right?
    %dd Yeah, you browsed to a page that doesn't exist on this server.

    %dt What can I do?
    %dd
      As a very good book says on its cover:
      = succeed "." do
        %strong DON'T PANIC
      / if you didn't get the reference you aren't as nerd as you should be
      You should probably just go back to
      %a{ :href => root_path, :rel => "home" } the projects list
      or, alternatively, go
      = succeed "." do
        %a{ :href => request.referer } back from whence you came

    %dt
      What the hell is
      = succeed "?" do
        %strong report_card
    %dd
      report_card is a gem for generating
      %a{ :href => "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Software_metric" } Software metrics
      using the excellent
      = succeed "." do
        %a{ :href => "http://github.com/jscruggs/metric_fu" } metric_fu
      For more information about this project, check out
      = succeed "." do
        %a{ :href => "http://github.com/PerfectlyNormal/report_card" } the GitHub page